Spam and Eggs here again and I thought I'd give you a unedited (except for total size) practice canvas I made today. Normally those are mixed with reference drawings, studies and exercises, but this time I made one that is nothing but anthros so I though I'd share.
I think I'm making good progress, but it's a good news bad news situation right now.
The good news: I found the two core issues that kicked my ass all these years ago and made me quit until /hmofa/ motivated me pick up drawing again.
The bad news: Those are rather significant problems that have deeply ingrained themselves and will take a lot of time to expunge completely. I'm not sure how to explain with words, since it's mostly issues with mentality and being in the right headspace. But the gist of it is that my mind tends to wander off and waste resources that I should use for the task at hand. The other one is constantly failing to visualize what I want to draw as w whole and tunnel visioning on parts of it.
Today I had those under control, but it is a massive effort to constantly look over my shoulder and remind myself of what I should and shouldn't do. The nice thing about is that I can practice fighting these two demons everywhere and everytime and it also benefits me in all walks of life, even when at work or playing vidya. Speaking of which, more bad news: I relapsed on my Nuclear Throne addiction.

Also, a rundown of my alchemical glyphs:

! = good
~ = so and so
? = not sure
X = bad

|-> <-| = scale down part

I owe you all a lot, I didn't realize how much I missed drawing until I started again.

Have a good one, /hmofa/ and thank you.

Anonymous Sat 03 Apr 2021 19:46:54 No.37624546 Report

>>37623740
I think the Galilean moons would be the best choice for that setting. They could be reached with nuclear rockets of that time in a reasonable timeframe. Any communication out past the asteroid belt would require highly dedicated infrastructure (probably laser communication systems) and from Jupiter would experience anywhere from a little over thirty minutes delay one way up to almost an hour, depending on where Jupiter and Earth are in their orbits. Since Jupiter receives so little light in comparison to Earth they'd definitely be getting their power from a nuclear reactor, not solar panels.
I don't know how much you plan to explore the technological side of the world in the story, but if you do then don't mention the Shuttle. Have it not exist at all. It might seem silly but for an alternate history sci-fi story that little bit will go a long way towards helping make it more believable, especially to the people who are into really hard sci-fi.
Also, a couple other questions: How do you plan to handle the USSR and the cold war? How do you plan to handle the aliens?
